div.p:
Extent should be specified for the works wherever possible;
  obligatory for works with digital text provided, after the edition
  statement:

References to these witnesses can be done with a link directly to a
  witness's or a listWit's
  @xml:id like in LIT2317Senodo and LIT1709Kebran.

@active should contain the xml:id of the
  current item. @passive should contain the ids
  of the related works, people, places, separated by a space

item.p:
if it is an ancient place but not in ethiopia, like Jordan,
      Rome, etc. then search pleaides and use a pleiades id prefixed
      with pleaides: e.g. for Jordan River use plaeides:687932

div.p:
Text is entered in the body of a TEI file
  under into a div[@type='edition'] . Each text
  part should be contained into a div.
  divs should always be well nested one into the
  other. These will always take a
  @subtype='textpart' and a
  @subtype with the desired value. There should
  always be also a @n identifying for example chapter 3 as well as a
  @corresp pointing to the appropriate
  msPart or msItem
